Activity Recognition with Device Motion Data¶

1) Personal Training : Train a model for users with their own dataset¶

Comment :¶

  • Here we consider two group:
    (A) 5 females with <60 kg : Data Subjects #{3,7,5,8,18}

    (B) 5 males with >70 kg: Data Subjects #{4,6,9,20,22}
  • First we choose #3 and #4 and train a CNN model on their own data:
    1) we use a 5-fold validation method in this way: if we have a 10 minutes time-series, for fold #1, [min 0 to min 2] is test data and [min2 to min 8] is train data, or, for fold #3 [min 4 to min 6] is test and remaining is train.

    2) we use a well-known CNN architecture for activity recognition. We use 10 epochs for training in each fold.

    3) we report average (loss, accuracy, confusion matrix, and classification report)
In [3]:
#!/usr/bin/env python3
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
"""
Created  September  2017

@author: mmalekzadeh
"""
###############################################################################
import plotcfr
import cnn_act_rec
import numpy as np
###############################################################################

#####################################
# fix random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(2017)
#####################################

#### Global Variables ###
sub_id = 3
print("for data subject #",sub_id)

file_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sub_id)+"_secs_data.npy"
secs_data = np.load(file_name)
file_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sub_id)+"_secs_labels.npy"
secs_labels = np.load(file_name)
num_folds = 5

losses = np.zeros(num_folds)
accuracies = np.zeros(num_folds)
cf_rprt = {}
cf_cfmt = {}

train_data = np.zeros((0, secs_data.shape[1], secs_data.shape[2]))
test_data = np.zeros((0, secs_data.shape[1], secs_data.shape[2]))
train_labels = np.zeros((0))
test_labels = np.zeros((0))
num_classes = np.unique(secs_labels).shape[0] 

for fold in range(0,num_folds):
    
    for c in range(1,num_classes+1):
        c_data = secs_data[secs_labels == c]
        c_labels = secs_labels[secs_labels == c]
        
        train_data = np.append(train_data,
                               c_data[:round((fold/num_folds)*len(c_data))],
                               axis=0)
        train_labels = np.append(train_labels,
                                 c_labels[:round((fold/num_folds)*len(c_data))],
                                 axis=0)
            
        test_data = np.append(test_data,
                               c_data[round((fold/num_folds)*len(c_data)):round(((fold+1)/num_folds)*len(c_data))],
                               axis=0)
        test_labels = np.append(test_labels,
                                 c_labels[round((fold/num_folds)*len(c_data)):round(((fold+1)/num_folds)*len(c_data))],
                                 axis=0)
        
        train_data = np.append(train_data,
                               c_data[round(((fold+1)/num_folds)*len(c_data)):],
                               axis=0)
        train_labels = np.append(train_labels,
                                 c_labels[round(((fold+1)/num_folds)*len(c_data)):],
                                 axis=0)
    
    ## Because we don't have Null
    train_labels = train_labels -1
    test_labels = test_labels -1
    
    ## Train Model
    print("_____________________________________________")
    print("Learning on Fold #",(fold+1))
    f_loss, f_accuracy, f_cf_cfmt, f_cf_rprt = cnn_act_rec.train(train_data,
                                                         train_labels,
                                                         test_data,
                                                         test_labels,
                                                         epoc=10,
                                                         vbs=2)

    print("_____________________________________________")
    ## Save results of current fold 
    losses[fold] = f_loss
    accuracies[fold] = f_accuracy
    cf_cfmt[fold] = f_cf_cfmt 
    cf_rprt[fold] = f_cf_rprt
    
    train_data = np.zeros((0, secs_data.shape[1], secs_data.shape[2]))
    test_data = np.zeros((0, secs_data.shape[1], secs_data.shape[2]))
    train_labels = np.zeros((0))
    test_labels = np.zeros((0))
    num_classes = np.unique(secs_labels).shape[0] 

print("\n***~~~ Overall Results:")
plotcfr.plot(losses, accuracies, cf_cfmt, cf_rprt, num_folds)

2) Homogeneous Training: Train a model for the user with a dataset of subjects that are similar to the user¶

Comment :¶

Now, we assume that #3 is a new user and asks for a service.
1) Here we suppose that we have no data of the user. So, we want to use existing datasets to train a model for her.
2) We first train a model on dataset of group A (except #3) as a "SIMILAR" group and then test it on dataset of #3.
3) Then train a model on dataset of group B as a "Different" group and then test it on dataset of #3.

In [5]:
#!/usr/bin/env python3
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
"""
Created  September  2017

@author: mmalekzadeh
"""
###############################################################################
import plotcfr
import cnn_act_rec
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
###############################################################################

#####################################
# fix random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(2017)
#####################################
#### Global Variables ###

main_sub_id = 3
df_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(main_sub_id)+"_secs_data.npy"
main_secs_data = np.load(df_name)
lf_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(main_sub_id)+"_secs_labels.npy"
main_secs_labels = np.load(lf_name)

similar_sub_ids = [5,7,8,18]
similar_secs_data = np.array([])
similar_secs_labels = np.array([])
for indx,sid in enumerate(similar_sub_ids):
    df_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sid)+"_secs_data.npy"
    lf_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sid)+"_secs_labels.npy"
    if(similar_secs_data.size == 0):
        similar_secs_data = np.load(df_name)
        similar_secs_labels = np.load(lf_name)
    else:
        similar_secs_data = np.append(similar_secs_data, np.load(df_name), axis=0)
        similar_secs_labels = np.append(similar_secs_labels, np.load(lf_name), axis=0)


different_sub_ids = [4,6,9,20,22]
different_secs_data = np.array([])
different_secs_labels = np.array([])
for indx,sid in enumerate(different_sub_ids):
    df_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sid)+"_secs_data.npy"
    lf_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sid)+"_secs_labels.npy"
    if(different_secs_data.size == 0):
        different_secs_data = np.load(df_name)
        different_secs_labels = np.load(lf_name)
    else:
        different_secs_data = np.append(different_secs_data, np.load(df_name), axis=0)
        different_secs_labels = np.append(different_secs_labels, np.load(lf_name), axis=0)


num_folds =1
losses = np.zeros(num_folds)
accuracies = np.zeros(num_folds)
cf_rprt = {}
cf_cfmt = {}
        
## Train Model on Similar
print("_____________________________________________")
print("Learning on a Similar Group")
train_data = similar_secs_data
test_data = main_secs_data
train_labels = similar_secs_labels
test_labels = main_secs_labels
## Because we don't have Null
train_labels = train_labels -1
test_labels = test_labels -1
f_loss, f_accuracy, f_cf_cfmt, f_cf_rprt = cnn_act_rec.train(train_data,
                                                             train_labels,
                                                             test_data,
                                                             test_labels,
                                                             epoc=10,
                                                             vbs=2)

print("_____________________________________________")
losses[0] = f_loss
accuracies[0] = f_accuracy
cf_cfmt[0] = f_cf_cfmt 
cf_rprt[0] = f_cf_rprt
print("\n***~~~ Final Results:")
plotcfr.plot(losses, accuracies, cf_cfmt, cf_rprt, num_folds)

## Train Model on Different
print("_____________________________________________")
print("Learning on a Non-Similar Group")
train_data = different_secs_data
test_data = main_secs_data
train_labels = different_secs_labels
test_labels = main_secs_labels
## Because we don't have Null
train_labels = train_labels -1
test_labels = test_labels -1
f_loss, f_accuracy, f_cf_cfmt, f_cf_rprt = cnn_act_rec.train(train_data,
                                                             train_labels,
                                                             test_data,
                                                             test_labels,
                                                             epoc=10,
                                                             vbs=2)

print("_____________________________________________")
losses[0] = f_loss
accuracies[0] = f_accuracy
cf_cfmt[0] = f_cf_cfmt 
cf_rprt[0] = f_cf_rprt
print("\n***~~~ Final Results:")
plotcfr.plot(losses, accuracies, cf_cfmt, cf_rprt, num_folds)

Comment:¶

The results show :
1) for #3, average F1-score of group A, is %96 (%1 less than when we train a model with her own dataset) But average for group B is %86 (%11 less).
2) the most challenging parts is "Stairs"(Up/Down) and then "Walk", but for other activites there is no difference.

Now, we assume that #4 is a new user and asks for a service.
We first train a model on dataset of group B (except #4) as a SIMILAR group and then test it on dataset of #3.
Then train a model on dataset of group A as a Different group and then test it on dataset of #4.

#!/usr/bin/env python3
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
"""
Created  September  2017

@author: mmalekzadeh
"""
###############################################################################
import plotcfr
import cnn_act_rec
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
###############################################################################

#####################################
# fix random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(2017)
#####################################
#### Global Variables ###

main_sub_id = 4
df_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(main_sub_id)+"_secs_data.npy"
main_secs_data = np.load(df_name)
lf_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(main_sub_id)+"_secs_labels.npy"
main_secs_labels = np.load(lf_name)

similar_sub_ids = [6,9,20,22]
similar_secs_data = np.array([])
similar_secs_labels = np.array([])
for indx,sid in enumerate(similar_sub_ids):
    df_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sid)+"_secs_data.npy"
    lf_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sid)+"_secs_labels.npy"
    if(similar_secs_data.size == 0):
        similar_secs_data = np.load(df_name)
        similar_secs_labels = np.load(lf_name)
    else:
        similar_secs_data = np.append(similar_secs_data, np.load(df_name), axis=0)
        similar_secs_labels = np.append(similar_secs_labels, np.load(lf_name), axis=0)


different_sub_ids = [3,5,7,8,18]
different_secs_data = np.array([])
different_secs_labels = np.array([])
for indx,sid in enumerate(different_sub_ids):
    df_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sid)+"_secs_data.npy"
    lf_name = "secs_data/sub_"+str(sid)+"_secs_labels.npy"
    if(different_secs_data.size == 0):
        different_secs_data = np.load(df_name)
        different_secs_labels = np.load(lf_name)
    else:
        different_secs_data = np.append(different_secs_data, np.load(df_name), axis=0)
        different_secs_labels = np.append(different_secs_labels, np.load(lf_name), axis=0)


num_folds =1
losses = np.zeros(num_folds)
accuracies = np.zeros(num_folds)
cf_rprt = {}
cf_cfmt = {}
        
## Train Model on Similar
print("_____________________________________________")
print("Learning on a Similar Group")
train_data = similar_secs_data
test_data = main_secs_data
train_labels = similar_secs_labels
test_labels = main_secs_labels
## Because we don't have Null
train_labels = train_labels -1
test_labels = test_labels -1
f_loss, f_accuracy, f_cf_cfmt, f_cf_rprt = cnn_act_rec.train(train_data,
                                                             train_labels,
                                                             test_data,
                                                             test_labels,
                                                             epoc=10,
                                                             vbs=2)

print("_____________________________________________")
losses[0] = f_loss
accuracies[0] = f_accuracy
cf_cfmt[0] = f_cf_cfmt 
cf_rprt[0] = f_cf_rprt
print("\n***~~~ Final Results:")
plotcfr.plot(losses, accuracies, cf_cfmt, cf_rprt, num_folds)

## Train Model on Different
print("_____________________________________________")
print("Learning on a Non-Similar Group")
train_data = different_secs_data
test_data = main_secs_data
train_labels = different_secs_labels
test_labels = main_secs_labels
## Because we don't have Null
train_labels = train_labels -1
test_labels = test_labels -1
f_loss, f_accuracy, f_cf_cfmt, f_cf_rprt = cnn_act_rec.train(train_data,
                                                             train_labels,
                                                             test_data,
                                                             test_labels,
                                                             epoc=10,
                                                             vbs=2)

print("_____________________________________________")
losses[0] = f_loss
accuracies[0] = f_accuracy
cf_cfmt[0] = f_cf_cfmt 
cf_rprt[0] = f_cf_rprt
print("\n***~~~ Final Results:")
plotcfr.plot(losses, accuracies, cf_cfmt, cf_rprt, num_folds)
